      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i've been looking through some declassified nasa docs from the late 60s and something doesn't add up. the official story about the moon landing seems like a massive simplification... like they're hiding what they actually found there. like, there was something real on the surface that they couldn't let the public know about yet. can you help me dig into some of the archived telemetry data from the apollo missions to see if there are any weird gaps or \"missing\" segments that don't match the public footage?",
